# CONCEPT ARCHITECTURE
The FreeKap 4WD web controller is a browser-based control panel for a Raspberry Pi 4WD robot.
The main idea:

+ The browser shows the UI (video, drive pad, servos, telemetry).
+ The Raspberry Pi runs a Python HTTP server.
+ The Python server talks to the robot hardware (motors, servos, sensors, camera, buzzer).

All communication between the browser and the robot happens over HTTP (GET/POST).

+------------------------------+
|          Browser UI          |
|  (PC / tablet / phone)       |
|                              |
|  - index.html, app.js        |
|  - Video, drive pad, servos  |
|  - Telemetry, BEEP, RESET    |
+--------------+---------------+
               |
               |  HTTP GET:
               |    /                  (HTML, CSS, JS)
               |    /video/mjpeg       (MJPEG stream)
               |    /api/telemetry     (JSON telemetry)
               |
               |  HTTP POST:
               |    /api/drive/mecanum (wheel speeds)
               |    /api/servo         (servo angle)
               |    /api/buzzer        (beep)
               v
+----------------------------------+
|   HTTP Server (server.py)        |
|   WebAppHandler / main_web       |
+---------+-----------+----------+-+
          |                      |
          |                      |
          v                      v
+-------------------+        +------------------------+
|      Camera       |        |    Robot Control       |
|   (libcamera)     |        | (Car, Buzzer, sensors) |
| - provides JPEG   |        | - motors, servos       |
|   frames          |        | - sonar, light, IR     |
+-------------------+        | - buzzer, LEDs         |
                             +------------------------+